3574 /// evalBind - Handle the semantics of binding a value to a specific location.
3575 /// This method is used by evalStore and (soon) VisitDeclStmt, and others.
3576 void ExprEngine::evalBind(ExplodedNodeSet &Dst, const Stmt *StoreE,
3577  ExplodedNode *Pred,
3578  SVal location, SVal Val,
3579  bool atDeclInit, const ProgramPoint *PP) {
3580  const LocationContext *LC = Pred->getLocationContext();
3581  PostStmt PS(StoreE, LC);
3582  if (!PP)
3583  PP = &PS;
3584 
3585  // Do a previsit of the bind.
3586  ExplodedNodeSet CheckedSet;
3587  getCheckerManager().runCheckersForBind(CheckedSet, Pred, location, Val,
3588  StoreE, *this, *PP);
3589 
3590  StmtNodeBuilder Bldr(CheckedSet, Dst, *currBldrCtx);
3591 
3592  // If the location is not a 'Loc', it will already be handled by
3593  // the checkers. There is nothing left to do.
3594  if (!isa<Loc>(location)) {
3595  const ProgramPoint L = PostStore(StoreE, LC, /*Loc*/nullptr,
3596  /*tag*/nullptr);
3597  ProgramStateRef state = Pred->getState();
3598  state = processPointerEscapedOnBind(state, location, Val, LC);
3599  Bldr.generateNode(L, state, Pred);
3600  return;
3601  }
3602 
3603  for (const auto PredI : CheckedSet) {
3604  ProgramStateRef state = PredI->getState();
3605 
3606  state = processPointerEscapedOnBind(state, location, Val, LC);
3607 
3608  // When binding the value, pass on the hint that this is a initialization.
3609  // For initializations, we do not need to inform clients of region
3610  // changes.
3611  state = state->bindLoc(location.castAs<Loc>(),
3612  Val, LC, /* notifyChanges = */ !atDeclInit);
3613 
3614  const MemRegion *LocReg = nullptr;
3615  if (std::optional<loc::MemRegionVal> LocRegVal =
3616  location.getAs<loc::MemRegionVal>()) {
3617  LocReg = LocRegVal->getRegion();
3618  }
3619 
3620  const ProgramPoint L = PostStore(StoreE, LC, LocReg, nullptr);
3621  Bldr.generateNode(L, state, PredI);
3622  }
3623 }

3625 /// evalStore - Handle the semantics of a store via an assignment.
3626 /// @param Dst The node set to store generated state nodes
3627 /// @param AssignE The assignment expression if the store happens in an
3628 /// assignment.
3629 /// @param LocationE The location expression that is stored to.
3630 /// @param state The current simulation state
3631 /// @param location The location to store the value
3632 /// @param Val The value to be stored
3633 void ExprEngine::evalStore(ExplodedNodeSet &Dst, const Expr *AssignE,
3634  const Expr *LocationE,
3635  ExplodedNode *Pred,
3636  ProgramStateRef state, SVal location, SVal Val,
3637  const ProgramPointTag *tag) {
3638  // Proceed with the store. We use AssignE as the anchor for the PostStore
3639  // ProgramPoint if it is non-NULL, and LocationE otherwise.
3640  const Expr *StoreE = AssignE ? AssignE : LocationE;
3641 
3642  // Evaluate the location (checks for bad dereferences).
3643  ExplodedNodeSet Tmp;
3644  evalLocation(Tmp, AssignE, LocationE, Pred, state, location, false);
3645 
3646  if (Tmp.empty())
3647  return;
3648 
3649  if (location.isUndef())
3650  return;
3651 
3652  for (const auto I : Tmp)
3653  evalBind(Dst, StoreE, I, location, Val, false);

3656 void ExprEngine::evalLoad(ExplodedNodeSet &Dst,
3657  const Expr *NodeEx,
3658  const Expr *BoundEx,
3659  ExplodedNode *Pred,
3660  ProgramStateRef state,
3661  SVal location,
3662  const ProgramPointTag *tag,
3663  QualType LoadTy) {
3664  assert(!isa<NonLoc>(location) && "location cannot be a NonLoc.");
3665  assert(NodeEx);
3666  assert(BoundEx);
3667  // Evaluate the location (checks for bad dereferences).
3668  ExplodedNodeSet Tmp;
3669  evalLocation(Tmp, NodeEx, BoundEx, Pred, state, location, true);
3670  if (Tmp.empty())
3671  return;
3672 
3673  StmtNodeBuilder Bldr(Tmp, Dst, *currBldrCtx);
3674  if (location.isUndef())
3675  return;

3678  for (const auto I : Tmp) {
3679  state = I->getState();
3680  const LocationContext *LCtx = I->getLocationContext();
3681 
3682  SVal V = UnknownVal();

3687  }
3688

3690  ProgramPoint::PostLoadKind);
3691  }

3694 void ExprEngine::evalLocation(ExplodedNodeSet &Dst,
3695  const Stmt *NodeEx,
3696  const Stmt *BoundEx,
3697  ExplodedNode *Pred,
3698  ProgramStateRef state,
3699  SVal location,
3700  bool isLoad) {

3740 void ExprEngine::evalEagerlyAssumeBinOpBifurcation(ExplodedNodeSet &Dst,
3741  ExplodedNodeSet &Src,
3742  const Expr *Ex) {
3743  StmtNodeBuilder Bldr(Src, Dst, *currBldrCtx);
3744 
3745  for (const auto Pred : Src) {
3746  // Test if the previous node was as the same expression. This can happen
3747  // when the expression fails to evaluate to anything meaningful and
3748  // (as an optimization) we don't generate a node.
3749  ProgramPoint P = Pred->getLocation();
3750  if (!P.getAs<PostStmt>() || P.castAs<PostStmt>().getStmt() != Ex) {
3751  continue;
3752  }
3753 
3754  ProgramStateRef state = Pred->getState();
3755  SVal V = state->getSVal(Ex, Pred->getLocationContext());
3756  std::optional<nonloc::SymbolVal> SEV = V.getAs<nonloc::SymbolVal>();
3757  if (SEV && SEV->isExpression()) {
3758  const std::pair<const ProgramPointTag *, const ProgramPointTag*> &tags =
3759  geteagerlyAssumeBinOpBifurcationTags();
3760 
3761  ProgramStateRef StateTrue, StateFalse;
3762  std::tie(StateTrue, StateFalse) = state->assume(*SEV);
3763 
3764  // First assume that the condition is true.
3765  if (StateTrue) {
3766  SVal Val = svalBuilder.makeIntVal(1U, Ex->getType());
3767  StateTrue = StateTrue->BindExpr(Ex, Pred->getLocationContext(), Val);
3768  Bldr.generateNode(Ex, Pred, StateTrue, tags.first);
3769  }
3770 
3771  // Next, assume that the condition is false.
3772  if (StateFalse) {
3773  SVal Val = svalBuilder.makeIntVal(0U, Ex->getType());
3774  StateFalse = StateFalse->BindExpr(Ex, Pred->getLocationContext(), Val);
3775  Bldr.generateNode(Ex, Pred, StateFalse, tags.second);
3776  }
3777  }
3778  }
3779 }

3820  static bool nodeHasBugReport(const ExplodedNode *N) {
3821  BugReporter &BR = static_cast<ExprEngine &>(
3822  N->getState()->getStateManager().getOwningEngine()).getBugReporter();
3823 
3824  for (const auto &Class : BR.equivalenceClasses()) {
3825  for (const auto &Report : Class.getReports()) {
3826  const auto *PR = dyn_cast<PathSensitiveBugReport>(Report.get());
3827  if (!PR)
3828  continue;
3829  const ExplodedNode *EN = PR->getErrorNode();
3830  if (EN->getState() == N->getState() &&
3831  EN->getLocation() == N->getLocation())
3832  return true;
3833  }
3834  }
3835  return false;
3836  }
3837 
3838  /// \p PreCallback: callback before break.
3839  /// \p PostCallback: callback after break.
3840  /// \p Stop: stop iteration if returns @c true
3841  /// \return Whether @c Stop ever returned @c true.
3842  static bool traverseHiddenNodes(
3843  const ExplodedNode *N,
3844  llvm::function_ref<void(const ExplodedNode *)> PreCallback,
3845  llvm::function_ref<void(const ExplodedNode *)> PostCallback,
3846  llvm::function_ref<bool(const ExplodedNode *)> Stop) {
3847  while (true) {
3848  PreCallback(N);
3849  if (Stop(N))
3850  return true;
3851 
3852  if (N->succ_size() != 1 || !isNodeHidden(N->getFirstSucc(), nullptr))
3853  break;
3854  PostCallback(N);
3855 
3856  N = N->getFirstSucc();
3857  }
3858  return false;
3859  }
